Author: richardt#2807
Content: @Sdunbar I somewhat agree with you.  If you look at all the coins that pumped hard during the previous "altseasons", not many are left in the top 50 or even top 100 still.  Only a few managed to stay in the top (ETH, XMR, DASH, LTC, etc.) for whatever reason.  Perhaps these coins managed to gain enough followers/investors during the hype.  IMO, KMD kind of already missed the chance to stay in the top.  Next altseason, if it ever happens, will likely be a newer set of coins going up as the market goes through another cycle.  Not sure if KMD will ever see ATH again.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: the market of cryptocurrency is still in so early on it's time even after it's 10 years of existence, I can't image anyone accurately predicting where today's top and bottom project will be in next 10 years. But one thing I understand for sure is whichever projects will have continuous delivery on the technological advancements solving the problems in hand right now which needs to be solved to make it adoptable by as efficiently and effortlessly by the masses, will go the long way. It sure won't die or fad away in history. What percentage such projects will keep of the market is also uncertain, but sure even if such projects survive in such long term future, even being in single digit percentage will be enormously valuable with it's total market cap of that future pegged valued asset class or commonly used currency. In all of this game of future value increase, I don't see KMD going anywhere but more valued as time passes by, because it's definitely doesn't look like slowing down in innovating new solutions to current problems and keeping itself ahead in game as compare to any other project in industry. If it keeps doing that again and again repeatedly, as long as possible, it'll gain significant market share. Just don't be jealous or be worried with other competing projects in market with their today's market value. It's fine where they are today. try to help KMD if you believe in it all the ways you think it lacks or need improvement. It sure will surpass others in value too.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: What most forget in all this madness is that there is always a floor when it comes to price.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: If you only have marketing with no tech, the floor is going to much lower than some project with actual tech

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: When the markets start repricing tech innovation and utility and factoring in future usage, you will see KMD up there. For now it is just hype and hope that is driving this market. We should not change our focus to please people now whilst not building out our vision to serve users in the future.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content:
There are lots of projects out there, like waves, that is trying everything in their power to stay relevant, doing buy backs, inflating the currency to appease miners, doing air drops and everything they can to hype and pump the price. These are very short sighted tactics for a  project that has very little technical value. We should not stoop to that level.

We will let all these types of projects to die off whilst we build out what will be needed very soon.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content:
I truly believe KMD will have its time in the spotlight. We are gearing up for that and when people realize what is happening, it will be too late.

They can only hold back true innovation for so long, but when the masses use it, the game is over.
